Personal pronouns are often used instead of repeating a name in multiple sentences that are close together. This can help avoid repetition and ease the flow of sentences.
I ___ Yo
You ___ Tú / Usted / Ustedes
He ___ Él
She ___ Ella
We ___ Nosotros / Nosotras
They ___ Ellos / Ellas 
It ___ Él / Ello / Ella (animal o cosa)

Possessive pronouns are used to express ownership or possession of an object or idea.
Mine ___ Mío
Yours ___ Tuyo / De Ustedes / Suyo
His ___ De él / Suyo
Hers ___ De ella / Suyo
Ours ___ Nuestro
Theirs ___ De ellos / Suyo
Its ___ De él / De ella / Suyo

* This notebook is mine.
* Are you going to high school?
* He is my friend.
* That PC is yours?
* We went for ice cream.
* The thesis is hers.
* I go to bed early.

* Este cuaderno es mío.
* ¿Tú estás yendo al liceo?
* Él es mi amigo.
* ¿Ese PC es tuyo?
* Nosotros fuimos a comer helado.
* La tesis es suya.
* Yo me acuesto temprano.

* I used to play in my friend’s house.
* We used to travel to another states.
